cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.MM, cs.LG 

The paper focuses on learning deep representations for three major natural modalities: vision, sound, and language. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions using millions of sentences paired with images, which suggests involvement with natural language processing, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) another likely category. Additionally, the paper mentions using sound from videos, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the transferability of the learned representations, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
